fstests-utils <sub-cmd>

sub-cmds:
------------------
test        run -g auto in parallel + parallel retry; write digest + fold history
adhoc       run specific tests in parallel on the currently-up workers (no build / digest)
results     show diffs vs for-next baseline / verdict history (see `results usage`)
digest      build a structured <sha>.json from a raw result file
state       fold per-test verdict history (history.json) for a branch
backfill    one-time bootstrap: generate missing <sha>.json digests
cron        wrappers for systemd-user timer (cron/for-next runs daily)
kp          classify tests into known-problem tiers from history.json
interpret   read adhoc JSONL on stdin, annotate against KP baseline
